did.abstract: The papers consists of subject files, which include correspondence, maintained by Logue and his staff during his tenure as mayor of New Haven, Connecticut.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The papers consists of subject files, which include correspondence, maintained by Logue and his staff during his tenure as mayor of New Haven, Connecticut.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Frank Logue was born in Philadelphia on August 18, 1924. He attended Yale University, enlisted in the military after Pearl Harbor, and served as an infantry soldier in France. He returned to Yale Law School in 1948. Logue entered politics in 1953 and held a number of positions, serving on the New Haven Board of Aldermen from 1972-1975. He was mayor of New Haven from 1976 to 1979. Logue died in Hamden, Connecticut, on December 31, 2010.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright has been transferred to Yale University for unpublished materials authored or otherwise produced by the creator(s) of this collection. Copyright status for other collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The material is unprocessed and may contain sensitive information or be in a physical state that would prohibit use. Researchers wishing to request access should email mssa.assist@yale.edu requesting specific box numbers in order to initiate the review process, which may take several weeks.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Deposited by Frank Logue in 1979, gifted to Yale University in 1995.

odd.head: General
odd.p: Boxes 7-12, 19-24, and 31-36 were flood damaged. Reference archivists/researchers should be aware that some of the material in the flood damaged boxes does not correspond exactly to the folder listing, although most of it does. Particularly, folders which were listed in the original inventory as being in box 24, from "Bank - Connecticut Savings" to "Commissions - New Haven Green" are missing and were subsequently deleted from the inventory.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Frank Logue papers (MS 1178). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.
